stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> DoDCheckResultGenerated

    DoDCheckResultGenerated --> MapChecksTransform: level, fix, example\nfrom DoDCheckResult

    MapChecksTransform --> PhaseErrorsRecorded: mapChecksForErrorToon()\n+ appendErrorToon()

    PhaseErrorsRecorded --> BuildErrorAnalysis: Save to phase-errors.toon\nwith full check metadata

    BuildErrorAnalysis --> PassedFilterCheck: Iterate entry.checks\nfrom toonErrors

    PassedFilterCheck --> CountFailures: Filter: skip if\npassed===true

    CountFailures --> RealizeLevel: Use check.level ??\ndefault L1

    RealizeLevel --> BuildErrorHistory: Aggregate to PhaseErrorStats\nfor topFailure ranking

    BuildErrorHistory --> ExpandAllChecks: Flatten all entries +\nall checks recursively

    ExpandAllChecks --> ErrorHistoryArray: Create ErrorHistoryEntry[]\nwith phase, retry, check,\nlevel, passed, evidence

    ErrorHistoryArray --> WriteAnalyticsToon

    WriteAnalyticsToon --> TopFailureWrite: Parallel write:\ntopFailure[]
    WriteAnalyticsToon --> ErrorHistoryWrite: Parallel write:\nerrorHistory[]

    TopFailureWrite --> AnalyticsToonComplete
    ErrorHistoryWrite --> AnalyticsToonComplete

    AnalyticsToonComplete --> [*]


%% DECISIONS
%% --------
%% D1: mapChecksForErrorToon function external placement
%%     Location: error-toon.ts (not inline in lifecycle-next.ts)
%%     Rationale: Reduces lifecycle-next.ts from 199→194 lines (200-line constraint)
%%     Benefits: Type definition and mapping colocate in same module for cohesion
%%
%% D2: Worker execution order - sequential dependency chain
%%     Chain: Worker-1 (error-toon.ts types) → Worker-2 (lifecycle-next.ts + phase-analytics.ts)
%%     → Worker-3 (analytics-toon.ts output)
%%     Rationale: Type definitions (Worker-1) must precede usage (Worker-2),
%%     which must precede output generation (Worker-3)
%%     Parallelization blocked by import dependencies
%%
%% D3: ErrorHistoryEntry type location - phase-analytics.ts
%%     Alternative rejected: Define in error-toon.ts
%%     Reason: AnalyticsResult and ErrorHistoryEntry are tightly coupled;
%%     define together in phase-analytics.ts, import in analytics-toon.ts
%%
%% D4: buildErrorHistory function visibility - internal (non-export)
%%     Rationale: Encapsulation; function only called from buildAnalytics()
%%     within same module. No external callers require this function.
%%     Public API surface minimization follows single responsibility principle.
%%
%% D5: errorHistory default behavior - empty array []
%%     Implementation: analytics.errorHistory ?? [] in analytics-toon.ts
%%     Handles case where phase-errors.toon is missing or empty
%%     Safe fallback ensures robust TOON output even with zero error history
